article.headline: Samford 71, Tenn-Martin 66
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Randall Gulina scored 24 points and grabbed a game-high six rebounds to lead Samford to a 71-66 victory Thursday night over Tennessee-Martin. Samford (12-8, 9-2 Ohio Valley Conference) won its third straight and handed the Skyhawks (5-17, 3-9) their fourth straight loss and 10th of their last 12. Gulina made five of six free throws in the final 15 seconds to preserve the win after Tennessee-Martin pulled to within 66-64 on a 3-pointer by Gerald Robinson. Martin's last lead was 49-48 on a 3-pointer by Joseph Bailey, his only basket of the game. Travis Peterson and Curtis West scored 13 apiece for Samford and Jerry Smith added 10. The Skyhawks, who led 29-26 at halftime, had balanced scoring with Cleve Woodfork hitting 13 and Zerek Knight, Spencer Harris, Robinson and Will Lewis adding 10 each. There were 11 ties and six lead changes.
